WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.320 --> 00:00:02.250
- [Voiceover] Mohamed
decides to track the number

00:00:02.250 --> 00:00:05.019
of leaves on the tree in
his backyard each year.

00:00:05.176 --> 00:00:08.372
The first year, there were 500 leaves.

00:00:08.853 --> 00:00:10.580
Each year thereafter, the number of leaves

00:00:10.580 --> 00:00:14.101
was 40% more than the year before.

00:00:14.481 --> 00:00:17.325
Let n be a positive integer,
and let f of n denote

00:00:17.325 --> 00:00:19.215
the number of leaves on
the tree in Mohamed's

00:00:19.215 --> 00:00:22.634
back yard in the nth year
since he started tracking it.

00:00:23.339 --> 00:00:26.840
The expression f of n defines a sequence.

00:00:26.894 --> 00:00:29.339
What kind of sequence is f of n?

00:00:29.719 --> 00:00:31.059
So, some of you might be able to

00:00:31.059 --> 00:00:31.933
think about this in your head.

00:00:31.933 --> 00:00:34.473
Each successive year we're growing by 40%,

00:00:34.473 --> 00:00:36.978
that's the same thing
as multiplying by 1.4.

00:00:37.276 --> 00:00:39.450
Each successive term we're multiplying

00:00:39.450 --> 00:00:41.844
or dividing by the same number.

00:00:41.844 --> 00:00:43.126
Well, that's going to be geometric.

00:00:43.567 --> 00:00:45.219
Let's make that a little
bit more tangible,

00:00:45.416 --> 00:00:46.641
just in case.

00:00:46.675 --> 00:00:48.998
So, let's make a little table here.

00:00:49.865 --> 00:00:51.558
So, table.

00:00:51.714 --> 00:00:54.890
So, this is n and this is f of n.

00:00:55.351 --> 00:00:57.084
So when n is equal to one,

00:00:57.139 --> 00:00:59.989
the first year, n equals
one, there were 500 leaves.

00:01:00.308 --> 00:01:01.838
F of n is 500.

00:01:02.340 --> 00:01:03.681
Now, when n is equal to two we're going

00:01:03.681 --> 00:01:05.875
to grow by 40%, which is the same thing

00:01:05.875 --> 00:01:08.035
as multiplying by 1.4.

00:01:08.760 --> 00:01:12.327
So 500 times 1.4, let's
do 40% of 500 is 200,

00:01:12.327 --> 00:01:14.298
so we're going to grow by 200, so we're

00:01:14.298 --> 00:01:16.011
going to go to 700.

00:01:16.431 --> 00:01:19.194
Then in year three, we're
going to grow by 40%

00:01:19.194 --> 00:01:23.981
of 700, which is 280, so
it's going to grow to 980.

00:01:23.981 --> 00:01:28.376
Notice it's definitely not
an arithmetic sequence.

00:01:28.573 --> 00:01:30.300
An arithmetic sequence, we would be adding

00:01:30.300 --> 00:01:32.425
or subtracting the same amount every time,

00:01:32.425 --> 00:01:33.198
but we're not.

00:01:33.198 --> 00:01:35.371
Here, from 500 to 700, we grew by 200,

00:01:35.371 --> 00:01:37.856
and then from 700 to 980, we grew by 280.

00:01:38.135 --> 00:01:40.085
Instead, we're multiplying or dividing by

00:01:40.085 --> 00:01:41.467
the same amount each time.

00:01:41.467 --> 00:01:43.748
In this case, we're multiplying by 1.4,

00:01:44.067 --> 00:01:45.861
by 1.4 each time.

00:01:45.916 --> 00:01:47.751
So we are clearly geometric.

00:01:47.968 --> 00:01:49.756
Depending on your answer
to the question above,

00:01:49.756 --> 00:01:51.869
the recursive definition
of the sequence can have

00:01:51.869 --> 00:01:53.535
one of the following two forms.

00:01:53.535 --> 00:01:55.221
Well this is the arithmetic form, which

00:01:55.221 --> 00:01:57.009
we know isn't the case,
so it's going to be

00:01:57.009 --> 00:01:58.437
in the geometric form.

00:01:59.264 --> 00:02:01.215
And then they ask us, what are the values

00:02:01.215 --> 00:02:03.551
of the parameters A
and B for the sequence?

00:02:03.551 --> 00:02:06.842
So we have our base case
here, f of n is going to be

00:02:06.842 --> 00:02:09.246
equal to A when n is equal to one.

00:02:09.484 --> 00:02:11.190
Well, we know that when n equals one,

00:02:11.190 --> 00:02:14.400
we had 500 leaves on the
tree so A, this A over here,

00:02:14.400 --> 00:02:18.912
is 500, so A is 500,

00:02:19.637 --> 00:02:21.226
and then if we're not in the base case

00:02:21.226 --> 00:02:22.485
for any other year,

00:02:22.485 --> 00:02:24.720
we are going to have,
let's see, it's going to be

00:02:24.720 --> 00:02:27.814
the previous year, the
previous year times what?

00:02:28.418 --> 00:02:31.039
It's going to be the
previous year grown by 40%,

00:02:31.039 --> 00:02:34.860
to grow by 40%, you're
going to multiply by 1.4

00:02:34.935 --> 00:02:37.989
so B is going to be 1.4.

00:02:38.023 --> 00:02:39.445
You take the previous
year and you multiply

00:02:39.445 --> 00:02:41.565
by 1.4 for any other year,

00:02:41.640 --> 00:02:43.291
any year other than n equals one.

00:02:43.712 --> 00:02:46.989
So, B is equal to 1.4, and we're done.

00:02:47.389 --> 00:02:48.425
